  breakup and reformation during the cambrian , laurasia was largely located in equatorial latitudes and began to break up , with north china and siberia drifting into latitudes further north than those occupied by continents during the previous 500 million years .

sometimes a great ocean : ( sarah of the clue crew shows a map on the monitor . )   during the mesozoic , the tethys sea separated the northern supercontinent of laurasia from this continent that contained what are now africa & south america

